us.com/index/1926/the-eee-pad-transformer-has-arrived/ |archive-date=29 August 2011 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref><br/>\n'''2011-05-07:''' France, Sweden<br/>\n'''2011-05-24:''' Australia|unitssold    =|service      =}}\nThe '''Asus Eee Pad Transformer''' (TF101) is an [[Android (operating system)|Android]] [[tablet computer]] announced at [[Consumer Electronics Show#2011|CES 2011]] and launched on 30 March 2011.<ref name=\"slashgear\">{{cite web|last=Davies|first=Chris|title=Asus Eee Pad Transformer first-impressions (Video)|url=http://www.slashgear.com/asus-eee-pad-transformer-first-impressions-video-30143387/|accessdate=31 March 2011}}</ref>  The Transformer design includes an optional docking keyboard.\n\n=== Asus Eee Pad Transformer Prime (TF201) ===\n{{Infobox information appliance\n| name         = Asus Eee Pad Transformer Prime\n| logo         = \n| image        =[[File:ASUS Eee Pad Transformer Prime.jpg|250px]]\n| caption      = Asus Eee Pad Transformer Prime\n| developer    = [[Asus]]\n| manufacturer =\n| type         = [[tablet computer|Tablet]], [[portable media player|media player]], [[personal computer|PC]]\n| releasedate  = 1 December 2011 ([[Republic of China|Taiwan]])<ref name=\"Engadget staff\">{{cite web |url=https://www.engadget.com/2011/12/01/asus-eee-pad-transformer-prime-review/ |title=Asus Eee Pad Transformer Prime review |author=Engadget staff |date=1 December 2011 |publisher=Engadget |accessdate=1 December 2011}}</ref> <br>{{Start date|df=yes|2011|12|12}} (United States online)<ref name=\"VergeRelease\">{{cite web|last=Bohn|first=Dieter|title=Asus Transformer Prime release date official: Dec. 12 online, Dec 19 retail|url=https://www.theverge.com/2011/12/1/2602224/asus-transformer-prime-us-release-date-official-dec-12-online-dec-19|publisher=The Verge|accessdate=15 January 2012|date=1 December 2011}}</ref> \n| lifespan     =\n| media        =\n| os           = [[Android (operating system)|Android]] 4.1.1<ref name=\"Engadget Jelly Bean Update\">{{cite web |url=https://www.engadget.com/2012/09/27/asus-transformer-prime-tf201-gets-android-4-1-1-jelly-bean-updat/|title=ASUS Transformer Prime TF201 gets Android 4.1.1 Jelly Bean update |author=Michael Gorman |date=27 September 2012 |publisher=Engadget |accessdate=14 October 2012}}</ref>\n| power        = \n| cpu          = 1.3 [[GHz]] [[quad-core]] [[Nvidia]] [[Tegra 3]] T30\n| storage      = [[Flash memory]]<br />32 or 64 [[gigabyte|GB]] and [[microSD]] slot\n| memory       = 1 GB\n| display      = 10.1\" LED Backlit screen with Super IPS+ (1280 x 800) 10 finger multi-touch [[Gorilla Glass]]\n| graphics     = [[GeForce]] ULP\n| sound        = monaural speaker, microphone, headset jack\n| input        = \n* 10 finger [[Multi-touch]] [[touchscreen|screen]]\n* dock [[computer keyboard|keyboard]] + [[touchpad]]\n* [[Compass]]\n* GPS receiver (removed from spec on US website - see hardware issue)\n* [[low-key lighting|Ambient light]] sensors\n* 3-axis [[accelerometer]]-[[gyroscope]]\n| camera = '''Back''': 8 [[megapixel|MP]] [[autofocus]]  <br/> 1080p video recording\n'''Front''': 1.9 MP for video calls\n| connectivity = \n* [[Bluetooth]] 2.1\n* micro [[HDMI]]\n* Dock 1x [[Universal Serial Bus|USB]] 2.0\n* [[Digital Living Network Alliance|DLNA]]\n* [[Wi-Fi]] [[802.11n|802.11b/g/n]]\n| service      =\n| dimensions   = '''Tablet''' <br /> {{convert|263|mm|in|abbr=on}} H<br />{{convert|180.8|mm|in|abbr=on}} W<br />{{convert|8.3|mm|in|abbr=on}} <br /> '''Keyboard''' <br /> {{convert|263|mm|in|abbr=on}} H<br />{{convert|180.8|mm|in|abbr=on}} W<br />{{convert|10.4|mm|in|abbr=on}}\n| weight       = '''Tablet''': {{convert|586|g|oz|abbr=on}} <br /> '''Keyboard''': {{convert|537|g|oz|abbr=on}}\n| predecessor  = [[Asus Eee Pad Transformer]]\n| successor    = [[Asus Transformer Pad Infinity]]\n| related      = [[Asus Transformer Pad TF300T]]\n| website      = {{URL|eee.asus.com/eeepad/transformer-prime}}\n}}\nThe '''Asus Eee Pad Transformer Prime''' (TF201) is the world's first Android [[tablet computer]] with a [[multi-core processor|quad-core]] processor, and a successor to the dual-core [[Asus Eee Pad Transformer]]. It runs [[Android version history#Android 4.1 Jelly Bean .28API level 16.29|Android 4.1]]. The Transformer Prime was announced by Asus on 9 November 2011. It was released in [[Republic of China|Taiwan]] on 1 December 2011,<ref name=\"Engadget staff\"/> and in Canada and the United States during the week of 19 December 2011.<ref name=\"Engadget staff\"/>\n\n=== Asus Transformer Pad TF300T (TF300T) ===\n{{Infobox information appliance\n| name         = Asus Transformer Pad TF300T\n| logo         =\n| image        = [[File:ASUS TF300 10.1 jeh.jpg|200px]]\n| caption      = Asus Eee Pad Transformer TF300T\n| developer    = [[Asus]]\n| manufacturer =\n| type         = Convertible [[Tablet computer|tablet]]\n| releasedate  = \n| lifespan     =\n| unitssold    = \n| media        =\n| os           = [[Android (operating system)|Android]] 4.0 (upgradable to 4.2)\n| power        = 10 hours; 22&nbsp;Wh [[lithium-ion polymer battery|Li-polymer]] battery, 15 hours with dock\n| cpu          = 1.3 [[GHz]] quad-core [[Nvidia]] [[Tegra 3]] T30L\n| storage      = [[Flash memory]]<br />16 or 32 [[gigabyte|GB]], [[microSD]] slot (dock full size [[Secure Digital|SD]] slot), unlimited Asus WebStorage\n| memory       = 1 [[gigabyte|GB]]\n| display      = 1280\u00d7800 [[pixel|px]] [[ Light-emitting diode|LED]] ([[aspect ratio (image)|aspect ratio]] 16:10) IPS (brightness 350 nits), {{convert|10.1|in|cm|abbr=on}} diagonal, 149&nbsp;[[pixel density|PPI]] not [[Gorilla Glass]]\n| graphics     = ULP [[GeForce]]\n| sound        = stereo speakers(not separated), microphone, headset jack\n| input        = \n* [[Multi-touch]] [[touchscreen|screen]]\n* dock keyboard + [[touchpad]]\n* [[compass]]\n* GPS receiver\n* [[low-key lighting|Ambient light]] sensors\n* 3-axis [[accelerometer]]-[[gyroscope]]\n| camera       = '''Rear:''' 8 [[megapixel|MP]] [[autofocus]] <br/>\n'''Front:''' 1.2 MP\n| connectivity = \n* [[Bluetooth]] V3.0+EDR\n* micro [[HDMI]] 1.3a\n* Dock 1x [[Universal Serial Bus|USB]] 2.0\n* [[Digital Living Network Alliance|DLNA]]\n* [[Wi-Fi]] [[802.11n|802.11b/g/n]]\n| service      =\n| dimensions   = {{convert|263|mm|in|abbr=on}} H<br />{{convert|180|mm|in|abbr=on}} W<br />{{convert|9.9|mm|in|abbr=on}} D\n| weight       = {{convert|635|g|lb|abbr=on}}\n| related      = [[Asus Eee Pad Transformer Prime]]<br />[[Asus Transformer Pad Infinity]]\n| website      = [https://www.asus.com/Tablets_Mobile/ASUS_Transformer_Pad_TF300T/ Official website]\n}}\nThe '''Asus Transformer Pad TF300T''' is an [[Android (operating system)|Android]] [[tablet computer]] with a [[multi-core processor|quad-core]] processor, and a successor to [[Asus Eee Pad Transformer Prime]]. The Transformer design includes an optional docking keyboard. The Asus Transformer Pad TF300T was released on the market in the U.S.<ref>{{cite web|first1=Matt|last1=Hamblen|url=http://www.techhive.com/article/254448/asus_fifth_and_rising_in_tablet_market.html|title=Asus, Fifth and Rising in Tablet Market|website=techhive.com|accessdate=2015-10-06}}</ref> and Europe in May 2012.<ref>{{cite web|title=Asus Transformer Pad TF300T und TF300TG ab Mai erh\u00e4ltlich \u2013 LTE-Version folgt|language=de|accessdate=2015-10-06|website=t3n.de|url=http://t3n.de/news/asus-transformer-pad-tf300t-384059/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151007083750/http://t3n.de/news/asus-transformer-pad-tf300t-384059/|archive-date=2015-10-07|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n=== Asus Transformer Pad Infinity (TF700T) ===\n{{Infobox information appliance\n| name         = Asus Transformer Pad Infinity\n| logo         =\n| image        = \n| caption      = \n| developer    = [[Asus]]\n| manufacturer =\n| type         = [[Tablet computer|Tablet]], [[portable media player|media player]], [[personal computer|PC]]\n| releasedate  = \n| lifespan     =\n| unitssold    = \n| media