The manufacturer announced it at [[Consumer Electronics Show|CES]] 2012, less than a month after the original product launch, to launch Q2 2012.<ref name=\"CNET CES 2012\">{{cite web |url=http://ces.cnet.com/8301-33378_1-57354292/asus-transformer-prime-gets-major-screen-upgrade/?tag=mncol%3b5n |title=Asus Transformer Prime gets major screen upgrade |last=Franklin |first=Eric |publisher=CNET |date=9 January 2012 |accessdate=21 January 2012}}</ref>\n\n=== Asus Transformer Pad TF701T(TF701T) === \n{{Infobox information appliance\n| name         = Asus Transformer Pad TF701T\n| title        = \n| aka          = K00C\n| logo         = \n| image        = Asus_Transformer_Pad_TF701T_Tablet_and_Keyboard_Dock.png\n| caption      = \n| developer    = [[Asus]]\n| manufacturer = [[Asus]]\n| family       = \n| type         = Convertible [[Tablet computer|Tablet]], [[portable media player|media player]], [[personal computer|PC]]\n| generation   = \n| releasedate  = November 2013\n| lifespan     = \n| price        = \n| discontinued = \n| unitssold    = \n| unitsshipped = \n| media        = \n| os           = [[Android (operating system)|Android Jelly Bean]] 4.2.2 (upgradable to Android KitKat 4.4.2)\n| power        = 13 hours; 31&nbsp;Wh [[lithium-ion polymer battery|Li-polymer]] battery, 17 hours with dock\n| soc          = 1.9 [[GHz]] quad-core [[Cortex-A15]] [[Nvidia]] [[Tegra#Tegra 4|Tegra 4]] T114 (Wayne) chipset\n| cpu          = \n| memory       = 2 [[gigabyte|GB]]\n| storage      = Tablet : [[Flash memory]]<br />32 or 64 [[gigabyte|GB]] (eMMC) and 1 [[microSD]] slot (SDHC/SDXC) that supports up to 128GB, Mobile dock : 1 full size [[Secure Digital|SD]] slot,\n| memory card  =\n| display      = [[WQXGA]] (2560x1600 [[pixel|px]]), [[LED-backlit]] [[LCD]] screen (16:10 [[aspect ratio (image)|aspect ratio]]), {{convert|10.1|in|cm|abbr=on}} diagonal, [[IGZO]] [[IPS panel|IPS]], 300&nbsp;[[pixel density|PPI]] with [[Gorilla Glass]] 2\n| graphics     = 72 Core GeForce (VLIW-based VEC4 units)\n| sound        = Premium Speaker with [http://www.asus.com/sonicmaster/global/whats-sonicmaster/benefits/ SonicMaster technology] (Stereo speaker), microphone, audio jack (headphone + mic-in)\n| input        = * [[Multi-touch]] [[touchscreen|screen]]\n* Dock [[Keyboard (computing)|keyboard]] + [[touchpad]]\n* G sensor for LCD auto-orientation\n* [[Compass]] (E-compass sensor)\n* [[GPS]] and [[GLONASS]] receiver\n* [[low-key lighting|Ambient light]] sensors\n* 3-axis [[accelerometer]]-[[gyroscope]]\n| controllers  = \n| camera       = '''Back:''' 5 [[megapixel|MP]] [[autofocus]] (1080p recording)<br/>\n'''Front:''' 1.2 MP (720p video recording), for video calls\n| touchpad     = \n| connectivity = \n* [[Bluetooth]] V3.0+EDR\n* Micro [[HDMI]] 1.4a\n* 1x [[Universal Serial Bus|USB]] 3.0 (with dock)\n* [[Digital Living Network Alliance|DLNA]]\n* [[Wi-Fi]] [[802.11n|802.11a/b/g/n]]\n* Support [[Miracast]]\t\n| platform     = \n| service      = \n| dimensions   = {{convert|180.8|mm|in|abbr=on}} H<br />{{convert|263|mm|in|abbr=on}} W<br />{{convert|8.9|mm|in|abbr=on}} D\n| weight       = {{convert|585|g|lb|abbr=on}}\n| topgame      = \n| compatibility= \n| predecessor  = [[Asus Transformer Pad Infinity]]\n| successor    = \n| related      = \n| website      = [http://www.asus.com/Tablets/The_New_ASUS_Transformer_PadTF701T/ Official website]\n}}\nThe '''Asus Transformer Pad TF701T''' is an [[Android (operating system)|Android]] [[tablet computer]] made by [[Asus]], successor to the [[Asus Transformer Pad Infinity]]. The Transformer design includes a docking keyboard. The Asus Transformer Pad TF701T was released in the UK <ref>[http://www.slashgear.com/asus-transformer-pad-tf701t-release-set-for-october-21st-with-nvidia-tegra-4-15301467/ ASUS Transformer Pad TF701T release set for October 21st with NVIDIA Tegra 4], www.slashgear.com, retrieved on 2014-10-07.</ref> in October 2013 and in the U.S. in November 2013.<ref>[http://androidcommunity.com/asus-transformer-pad-tf701t-us-availability-coming-soon-20131025/ ASUS Transformer Pad TF701T US availability coming soon], androidcommunity.com, retrieved on 2014-10-07.</ref>\n\nThe tablet includes a Tegra 4 T114 processor clocked at 1.9 GHz, and an upgraded 2560\u00d71600 pixel resolution screen, increasing the pixel density to 300 PPI and a mobile dock. '''Asus Transformer Pad TF701T''' had powerful hardware for its time according to the reviewers and after being discontinued, the users could perform an unofficial system update using CyanogenMod 12.1 which enabled the user to install Android Lollipop 5.1.1.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://forum.xda-developers.com/transformer-tf701/orig-development/cyanogenmod-12-1-lollipop-unofficial-t3123748|title=CyanogenMod 12.1 - Lollipop - Discussion|website=XDA Developers|language=en|access-date=2019-04-29}}</ref>\n\nReception for the Asus Transformer Pad TF701T was generally mixed.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.notebookcheck.net/Review-Asus-Transformer-Pad-TF701T-Tablet.115868.0.html|title=Review Asus Transformer Pad TF701T Tablet|last=Moser|first=Michael|website=Notebookcheck|language=en|access-date=2019-05-13}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.techspot.com/products/tablets/asus-transformer-pad-tf701-tf701t.94778/|title=Asus Transformer Pad TF701 / TF701T|website=TechSpot|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-13}}</ref>\n\n== Asus Transformer Book ==\nAsus Transformer Book is a line of detachable 2-in-1s that run [[Microsoft Windows]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.asus.com/transformerbook/ |title=Asus Transformer Book - product list |accessdate=November 3, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141102204217/http://www.asus.com/transformerbook/ |archive-date=November 2, 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n=== Asus Transformer Book T100 (T100) ===\n{{Expand section|date=September 2019}}\n\n=== Asus Transformer Book T100 Chi (T100CHI) ===\n{{Infobox computer\n| name         = Asus Transformer Book T100 Chi (T100