ormer Prime''' (TF201) is the world's first Android [[tablet computer]] with a [[multi-core processor|quad-core]] processor, and a successor to the dual-core [[Asus Eee Pad Transformer]]. It runs [[Android version history#Android 4.1 Jelly Bean .28API level 16.29|Android 4.1]]. The Transformer Prime was announced by Asus on 9 November 2011. It was released in [[Republic of China|Taiwan]] on 1 December 2011,<ref name=\"Engadget staff\"/> and in Canada and the United States during the week of 19 December 2011.<ref name=\"Engadget staff\"/>\n\n=== Asus Transformer Pad TF300T (TF300T) ===\n{{Infobox information appliance\n| name         = Asus Transformer Pad TF300T\n| logo         =\n| image        = [[File:ASUS TF300 10.1 jeh.jpg|200px]]\n| caption      = Asus Eee Pad Transformer TF300T\n| developer    = [[Asus]]\n| manufacturer =\n| type         = Convertible [[Tablet computer|tablet]]\n| releasedate  = \n| lifespan     =\n| unitssold    = \n| media        =\n| os           = [[Android (operating system)|Android]] 4.0 (upgradable to 4.2)\n| power        = 10 hours; 22&nbsp;Wh [[lithium-ion polymer battery|Li-polymer]] battery, 15 hours with dock\n| cpu          = 1.3 [[GHz]] quad-core [[Nvidia]] [[Tegra 3]] T30L\n| storage      = [[Flash memory]]<br />16 or 32 [[gigabyte|GB]], [[microSD]] slot (dock full size [[Secure Digital|SD]] slot), unlimited Asus WebStorage\n| memory       = 1 [[gigabyte|GB]]\n| display      = 1280\u00d7800 [[pixel|px]] [[ Light-emitting diode|LED]] ([[aspect ratio (image)|aspect ratio]] 16:10) IPS (brightness 350 nits), {{convert|10.1|in|cm|abbr=on}} diagonal, 149&nbsp;[[pixel density|PPI]] not [[Gorilla Glass]]\n| graphics     = ULP [[GeForce]]\n| sound        = stereo speakers(not separated), microphone, headset jack\n| input        = \n* [[Multi-touch]] [[touchscreen|screen]]\n* dock keyboard + [[touchpad]]\n* [[compass]]\n* GPS receiver\n* [[low-key lighting|Ambient light]] sensors\n* 3-axis [[accelerometer]]-[[gyroscope]]\n| camera       