 [[Tablet computer|tablet]]\n| releasedate  =  Cancelled <ref name=\"TD300 cancelled\" />\n| lifespan     =\n| unitssold    =\n| media        =\n| os           = [[Android (operating system)|Android 4.2.2]]<br />[[Windows (operating system)|Windows 8.1]]\n| power        = 5 hours in Windows 8.1; 38&nbsp;Wh [[lithium-ion polymer battery|Li-polymer]] battery, 6 hours in Android\n| cpu          = [[Intel]] [[Core i7]]\n| storage      = [[Flash memory]]<br />128 [[gigabyte|GB]] [[Solid State Drive|SSD]], 1 [[terabyte|TB]] [[Hard Disk Drive|HDD]]\n| memory       = 4 [[gigabyte|GB]]\n| display      = 1920\u00d71080 [[pixel|px]] ([[aspect ratio (image)|aspect ratio]] 16:9), {{convert|13.3|in|cm|abbr=on}} diagonal\n| graphics     =  To be announced\n| sound        = speaker, microphone, headset jack\n| input        =\n* [[Multi-touch]] [[touchscreen|screen]]\n* dock keyboard + [[touchpad]]\n* [[compass]]\n* GPS receiver\n* [[low-key lighting|Ambient light]] sensors\n* 3-axis [[accelerometer]]-[[gyroscope]]\n| camera       = To be announced\n| connectivity =\n* [[Bluetooth]] V4.0+EDR\n* Full size [[HDMI]] 1.4\n* Dock 2x [[Universal Serial Bus|USB]] 2.0\n* Dock 1x [[Universal Serial Bus|USB]] 3.0\n* [[LAN]] [[Ethernet port]]\n* [[Digital Living Network Alliance|DLNA]]\n* [[Wi-Fi]] [[802.11ac]]\n| service      =\n| dimensions   = {{convert|216.3|mm|in|abbr=on}} H<br />{{convert|342.7|mm|in|abbr=on}} W<br />{{convert|12.9|mm|in|abbr=on}} D\n| weight       = {{convert|1900|g|lb|abbr=on}}\n| related      = [[Asus Transformer Pad Infinity]]\n| website      =\n}}\nThe '''Transformer Book Duet TD300''', was a 13.3 inch [[tablet computer]] that was developed by [[Asus]].<ref name=\"ndtv\">{{cite web | url=http://gadgets.ndtv.com/laptops/news/ces-2014-asus-transformer-book-duet-launched-with-dual-boot-android-windows-468086 | title=CES 2014: Asus Transformer Book Duet launched with dual-boot Android, Windows | publisher=New Delhi Television Limited | date=7 January 2014 | accessdate=7 January 2014 | author=Swamy, Rohan}}</ref><ref name=\"Verge1\">{{cite web | url=https://www.theverge.com/2014/1/6/5275730/the-asus-transformer-book-duet-hybrid-switches-between-windows-and-android | title=The Asus Transformer Book Duet hybrid can instantly switch between Windows and Android | publisher=The Verge | date=6 January 2014 | accessdate=6 January 2014 | author=Ingraham  Nathan}}</ref><ref name=\"PCmag\">{{cite web | url=https://www.pcmag.com/article2/0,2817,2429053,00.asp | title=Asus Transformer Book Duet Dual Boots With Windows 8.1, Android | publisher=PCmag | date=6 January 2014 | accessdate=7 January 2014}}</ref> The device used two [[operating systems]] interchangeably: [[Windows 8.1]] by [[Microsoft]], and [[Android 4.1]] by [[Google]].<ref name=\"Verge1\" /><ref name=\"PCmag\" /><ref name=\"Gizmodo\">{{cite web | url=http://www.gizmodo.com.au/2014/01/asus-transformer-book-duet-one-laptop-two-tablets-all-the-crazy/ | title=Asus Transformer Book Duet: One Laptop, Two Tablets, All The Crazy | publisher=Gizmodo | date=6 January 2014 | accessdate=6 January 2014 | author=Limer Eric}}</ref> The device featured a tablet screen and a detachable [[Computer keyboard|keyboard]].<ref name=\"ndtv\"/><ref name=\"PCmag\" /><ref name=\"Gizmodo\" /> The device was reported to be cancelled due to opposition from both Google and Microsoft in mid-March, 2014.<ref name=\"TD300 cancelled\">{{cite news|title=Microsoft and Google ruin Intel's plan for dual-OS tablets|url=https://www.theverge.com/2014/3/14/5507784/microsoft-and-google-ruin-intel-plan-for-dual-os-tablets|accessdate=30 March 2017|work=[[The Verge]]|date=Mar 14, 2014}}</ref>\n\n=== Asus Transformer Book T101 ===\n{{Infobox computer\n| name         = Asus Transformer Book T101\n| aka          = Transformer Book T101\n| developer    = [[Asus]]\n| manufacturer = Asus\n| release date  = \n| os           = [[Windows 10 Home]]<br>[[Windows 10 Pro]]\n| power        = \n| cpu          = Intel\u00ae Cherry Trail Quad-Core Z8350 Processor\n| memory       = 4 GB SDRAM\n| storage      = eMMC: 32GB / 64GB / 128GBEMMC\n| display      = 10.1\" (16:10) LED backlit HD (1280x800) 60\u00a0Hz Glare Panel with 60% NTSC<br>Support ASUS Splendid Technology With WideView Technology\n| graphics     = Integrated Intel HD Graphics\n| sound        = Built-in Stereo 1.5 W Speakers And Digital Array Microphone<br>Support Windows 10 Cortana with Voice<br>ASUS SonicMaster Technology\n| input        = 1 x COMBO audio jack<br>1 x USB 2.0 port(s)<br>1 x Micro USB<br>1 x micro HDMI<br>1 x micro SDXC card reader\n| controllers  = \n| camera       = 2 Mega Pixel web camera\n| touchpad     = Yes\n| dimensions   = Tablet: 10.27 x 6.88 x 0.35 inch (WxHxD)<br>Dock: 10.27 x 6.88 x 0.39 inch (WxDxH)\n| weight       = Tablet: 0.62 kg<br>Dock: 0.25 kg\n}}\n{{Expand section|date=September 2019}}\n\n=== Asus Transformer Mini T102 ===\n{{Infobox computer\n| name         = Asus Transformer Mini T102\n| aka          = Transformer Mini T102\n| developer    = [[Asus]]\n| manufacturer = Asus\n| release date  = \n| os           = [[Windows 10 Pro]]\n| power        = \n| cpu          = Intel\u00ae Cherry Trail Quad-Core Processor,\n| memory       = 4 GB LPDDR3 1600MHz SDRAM Onboard Memory\n| storage      = Tablet 32 GB, up to 128 GB EMMC\n| display      = 10.1\" (16:10) LED backlit HD (1280x800) 60\u00a0Hz Glossy Touchscreen with 60% NTSC<br>Support ASUS Splendid Technology With WideView Technology\n| graphics     = Integrated Intel HD Graphics\n| sound        = Built-in Stereo W Speakers And Digital Array Microphone<br>Support Windows 10 Cortana with Voice<br>ASUS SonicMaster Technology\n| input        = 1 x COMBO audio jack<br>1 x Type A USB3.0 (USB3.1 GEN1)<br>1 x micro HDMI<br>1 x Volume up/down<br>1 x micro USB<br>1 x micro SD card\n| controllers  = \n| camera       = HD Web Camera\n| touchpad     = Yes\n| dimensions   = Tablet: 261 x 172 x 10 mm (WxDxH)<br>Dock: 262 x 173 x 5.7 mm (WxDxH)\n| weight       = Tablet: 0.62 